{
  "doc_id": "16227",
  "text": "We nevertheless agree with the authors of [CITATION_1] that a refined theory which includes relativistic effects and properly treats the orbit of the projectile is needed and should be applied in the future, when high-precision results become available at next-generation radioactive nuclear beam facilities. The currently available data will be hardly affected due to rather large statistical and systematical uncertainties.",
